ming Insider |accessdate=May 3, 2019 |date=May 3, 2019 }}</ref>\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"| '''[[2020 Billboard Music Awards|2020]]'''\n| colspan=\"2\"|TBD\n| \n| \n| \n| \n| \n|\n|}\n\n==See also==\n* [[Billboard Live Music Awards|''Billboard'' Live Music Awards]]\n* [[Billboard Japan Music Awards|''Billboard'' Japan Music Awards]]\n* [[Billboard Latin Music Awards|''Billboard'' Latin Music Awards]]\n* [[Billboard Women in Music|''Billboard'' Women in Music]]\n* [[Billboard Indonesian Music Awards 2020|''Billboard'' Indonesia Music Awards 2020]]\n\n==Notes==\n{{Reflist|group=note}}\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n*{{Official website|http://www.billboardmusicawards.com/}}\n\n{{Billboard Music Awards}}\n{{Musicawards}}\n{{DISPLAYTITLE:''Billboard'' Music Award}}\n\n[[Category:Billboard Music Award| ]]\n[[Category:Billboard (magazine)]]\n[[Category:Fox Broadcasting Company original programming]]\n[[Category:American annual television specials]]\n[[Category:American Broadcasting Company original programming]]\n[[Category:Television series by Dick Clark Productions]]\n[[Category:Awards established in 1990]]\n[[Category:Awards disestablished in 2007]]\n[[Category:Awards established in 2011]]\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox award\n| name           = ''Billboard'' Music Awards\n| current_awards = 2019 Billboard Music Awards\n| image          = Billboard-music-awards-logo.png\n| imagesize      = 200px\n| alt            = \n| caption        = \n| description    = Outstanding chart performance\n| presenter      = [[Billboard (magazine)|''Billboard'']]\n| country        = United States\n| network        = [[Fox Broadcasting Company|Fox]] (1990\u20132006)<br />[[American Broadcasting Company|ABC]] (2011\u20132017)<br />[[NBC]] (2018\u2013present)\n| year           = {{start date and age|1990|12|10}}\n| website        = {{URL|billboardmusicawards.com}}\n}}\n{{Infobox election\n| election_name = Most recent ''Billboard'' Music Award winners\n| election_date = [[2019 Billboard Music Awards|May 1, 2019]]\n| type = primary\n| ongoing = no\n| previous_election = 2018 Billboard Music Awards\n| previous_year = 2018\n| next_election =\n| next_year = 2020\n| opinion_polls = \n| 1blank = Award\n| 2blank = Winner\n| image1 = [[File:Drake_at_The_Carter_Effect_2017_(36818935200)_(cropped).jpg|160x160px]]\n| 1data1 = [[Billboard Music Award for Top Artist|Top Artist]] & [[Billboard Music Award for Top Male Artist|Top Male Artist]]\n| 2data1 = [[Drake (musician)|Drake]]\n| image2 = [[File:Dangerous Woman Tour in Manchester4 (cropped).jpg|160x160px]]\n| 1data2 = [[Billboard Music Award for Top Female Artist|Top Female Artist]]\n| 2data2 = [[Ariana Grande]]\n| image4 = [[File:Drake_at_The_Carter_Effect_2017_(36818935200)_(cropped).jpg|160x160px]]\n| 1data4 = [[Billboard Music Award for Top Billboard 200 Album|Top ''Billboard'' 200 Album]]\n| 2data4 = [[Drake (musician)|Drake]]<br/>(''[[Scorpion (Drake album)|Scorpion]]'')\n| image5 = [[File:AdamLevine2011.jpg|160x160px]]\n| 1data5 = [[Billboard Music Award for Top Hot 100 Song|Top Hot 100 Song]]\n| 2data5 = [[Maroon 5]] featuring [[Cardi B]]<br/>(\"[[Girls Like You]]\")\n| title = Top Artist\n| before_election = [[Ed Sheeran]]\n| after_election = [[Drake (musician)|Drake]]\n| 1data3 = [[Billboard Music Award for Top New Artist|Top New Artist]]\n| 2data3 = [[Juice Wrld]]\n| image3 = [[File:Juice Wrld Interview.png|160x160px]]\n}}\nThe '''''Billboard'' Music Award''' is an honor given out annually by ''[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]'', a publication and [[Billboard charts|music popularity chart]] covering the music business. The ''Billboard'' Music Awards show had been held annually since 1990 and the event was formerly held in December<ref>{{Cite news |url=http://www.billboard.com/articles/news/bbma/7386047/top-billboard-music-award-winners-all-time-1990-2016 |title=Top Billboard Music Award Winners of All Time (1990\u20132016) |last=Caulfield |first=Keith |date=March 31, 2016 |work=Billboard |access-date=April 10, 2017}}</ref> until it went dormant in 2006. The awards returned in 2011 and are now held annually in May.\n\n==Awards process==\nUnlike other awards, such as the [[Grammy Award]], which determine nominations as a result of the highest votes received by the [[National Academy of Recording Arts and Sciences]], the ''Billboard'' Music Awards finalists are based on album and digital songs sales, streaming, radio airplay, touring, and social engagement. These measurements are tracked year-round by ''Billboard'' and its data partners, including [[Nielsen SoundScan|\nNielsen Music]] and [[Next Big Sound]]. The 2018 awards are based on the reporting period of April 8, 2017 through March 31, 2018.<ref>{{Cite news |url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/news/bbma/8343598/billboard-music-awards-2018-nominations-list |title=Billboard Music Awards 2018 Nominations: See the Full List |date=April 17, 2018 |work=Billboard |access-date=April 17, 2018}}</ref> Awards are given for the top album, artist and single in a number of different [[music genres]].\n{{Clear}}\n==Awards==\n{| class=\"wikitable\"  style=\"font-size:95%; width:100%; text-align:center\"\n|-\n! width=\"3%\"| #\n! width=\"4%\"| Year\n! width=\"4%\"| TV\n! width=\"12%\"| Top Artist<ref>*Artist of the Year winners (1995\u20132006) {{cite web|url=http://www.billboardmusicawards.com/winners-database/?winnerKeyword=&winnerYear=&winnerCategory=artist-of-the-year|title=Winners Database: Artist of the Year|work=Billboard Music Awards|accessdate=October 16, 2016}}\n*Top Artist winners (2011\u201316) {{cite web|url=http://www.billboardmusicawards.com/winners-database/?winnerKeyword=&winnerYear=&winnerCategory=top-artistr|title=Winners Database: Top Artist|work=Billboard Music Awards|accessdate=October 16, 2016}}</ref>\n!Top Male Artist\n!Top Female Artist\n!Top New Artist\n!Top Duo/Group\n! width=\"18%\"| Top Hot 100 Song\n! width=\"17%\"| Top ''Billboard'' 200 Album\n! width=\"12%\"| Mul